<h1>Portfolio Items</h1>

<%= link_to "Create New Item", new_portfolio_url %>

<% @portfolio_items.each do |portfolio_item| %>
    <p><%= link_to portfolio_item.title, portfolio_path(portfolio_item) %></p>
    <p><%= portfolio_item.subtitle %></p>
    <p><%= portfolio_item.body %></p>
    <%= image_tag portfolio_item.thumb_image unless portfolio_item.thumb_image.nil? %>
    <%= link_to "Edit", edit_portfolio_path(portfolio_item) %>
    <%= link_to 'Delete Portfolio Item', portfolio_path(portfolio_item), remote: true, data: {"turbo-method": :delete, confirm: 'Are you sure?'}, class: 'delete-link' %>
  <% end %>

    <%# data-turbo-action: Specifies the action to perform when navigating. For example, replace, advance, frame, etc.

    data-turbo-frame: Specifies the target Turbo frame for the navigation.

    data-turbo-method: Specifies the HTTP method to use for the action, such as get, post, put, delete, etc.

    data-confirm: Specifies a confirmation message to show to the user before performing the action. If the user confirms, the action proceeds; otherwise, it's canceled.

    data-disable-with: Changes the content of the element while the action is being processed. This is commonly used with form submissions.

    data-action: Specifies the action to be taken when an event is triggered on the element. This is commonly used with Stimulus controllers.

    data-controller: Specifies which Stimulus controller(s) should be applied to the element.

    data-target: Specifies which Stimulus target(s) should be used within the element. %>